# Mobile Hero Text Removal

## Issue
The client requested that no text should be displayed on the mobile hero section, only the video.

## Changes Made

### 1. Removed Text from Direct Implementation in page.tsx
- Removed the text overlay from the direct video implementation in page.tsx
- Replaced it with a comment indicating the client's request

### 2. Updated All Mobile Hero Components
- Removed text from BasicVideoHero.tsx
- Removed text from SimpleMobileHero.tsx
- Removed text from MobileHero.tsx
- Removed text from MobileHeroFallback.tsx

### 3. Maintained Fallback Images
- Kept the fallback images in place for when video fails to load
- Maintained the overlay for better contrast

## Files Modified
1. `src/app/page.tsx`
   - Removed text overlay from the direct video implementation

2. `src/components/home/BasicVideoHero.tsx`
   - Removed text overlay

3. `src/components/home/SimpleMobileHero.tsx`
   - Removed text overlay

4. `src/components/home/MobileHero.tsx`
   - Removed text overlay

5. `src/components/home/MobileHeroFallback.tsx`
   - Removed text overlay

## Key Changes
Replaced text overlay sections like:
```jsx
<div className="absolute inset-0 flex items-center justify-center z-20">
  <div className="flex flex-col items-center justify-center px-4 text-center">
    <p className="text-white/90 uppercase tracking-widest text-sm mb-4">
      Experience
    </p>
    
    <h1 className="text-white text-4xl font-playfair italic mb-6"
        style={{ textShadow: '0 2px 4px rgba(0,0,0,0.5)' }}>
      Exquisite Indian Cuisine
    </h1>
    
    <!-- More text content -->
  </div>
</div>
```

With:
```jsx
{/* No text overlay on mobile as per client request */}
```

## Result
The mobile hero section now shows only the video (or fallback image) without any text overlay, as requested by the client.
